      "content": "\"misalignment\" sounds a bit vague for a tech reporter to swallow. they're gonna dig into the logs. \n\nwhat if we just don't mention the S3 bucket or the misconfiguration at all? could we pivot this to be about a \"system optimization\" or a \"scheduled infrastructure upgrade\" where some metadata was temporarily accessible during the transition? if we frame it as us proactively working on the system, we might even keep the trust scores steady instead of just damage controlling.",
